Super Eagles forward, Kelechi Iheanacho, has been nominated for the Premier League Player of the Month award. Iheanacho netted five goals in three league fixtures for Leicester City in the month under review. He will be up against Manchester City’s Riyad Mahrez, Tottenham Hotspur’s Harry Kane, West Ham United’s Jesse Lingard, Leeds United’s Illan Meslier, Manchester United’s Luke Shaw, Brighton & Hove Albion’s Leandro Trossard and Chelsea’s Andreas Christensen for the prize. Iheanacho is also nominated for Goal of the Month. He ensured the Foxes got a point against Burnley on March with a stunning volley. His contributions in March took his Premier League tally to six goals after 16 appearances.